<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-523-701  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 523 701.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  Oct 23 1990 n1538* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (England) 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Retailing software off optical disks: Kode gets the maintenancecontract. (Kode Computers Ltd.)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Kode Computers Ltd. (contracts)Entertainment Express (contracts).andO;Topic:     Maintenance ContractsSoftware RetailingOptical DisksOn-SiteCopyingDistribution Management.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>RETAILING SOFTWARE OFF OPTICAL DISKS: KODEandM;GETS THE MAINTENANCE CONTRACTandM;Kode Computers Ltd, the service arm of Kode International Plc, has beenappointed by Entertainment Express to maintain its electronic softwaredistribution machines.andP;  Over a three-year period, the contract could be worthup to #3m, and it currently covers the 50 units which are in operation atJohn Menzies branches across the UK.andP;  The maintenance contract is effectiveduring shop hours with a maximum response time of four hours.andP;  The ElectronicDistribution Of Software system is a computer with an optical disk drive thatholds a number of encrypted software titles.andP;  When a title is chosen by awould-be buyer, it is decrypted, recorded and downloaded to a high-speedcassette or floppy disk drive, and all transactions are reported to a hostcomputer which monitors system security, performs accounting procedures andcompiles reports.andP;  Kode says that since all items are produced specificallyfor each customer, the system provides an effective way of balancing supplyand demand and saves storager space.andO;</TEXT></DOC>